|!Version |!Date |!Changes |
|0.1.6 |2026-04-15 |Image thumbnails respect EXIF orientation (`-auto-orient` added to `thumb-image` action). Portrait-tagged photos from phones/cameras now render upright instead of landscape. Finalize route (video-frame thumbnail resize) also uses `-auto-orient` as a safety net; video pipelines unaffected in practice since ffmpeg's autorotate is default-enabled and strips rotation metadata during frame extraction and downscaling |
|0.1.5 |2026-04-15 |PDF thumbnails now use `pdftoppm` (poppler-utils) instead of `magick`. Fixes `Unknown device: png16malpha` on systems with Ghostscript 10+ where ImageMagick's PDF delegate requests a legacy device. `thumb-pdf` action param renamed `resolution` → `maxdim` (pdftoppm takes a single scale value, not NxN); pdf.tid and docx.tid updated accordingly |
|0.1.4 |2026-04-15 |Fix: `scanDir` branch of pipeline executor filtered scanned files by the resolved output basename prefix. Previously, a shared output directory (e.g. `_generated/` for video downscale) could leak files from earlier uploads into the current step's artifact results, creating spurious tiddlers bound to the new source |
|0.1.3 |2026-04-14 |Downscale output to `_generated/` (survives frame cleanup). Draggable + resizable thumbnail selection panel (JS). ffmpeg `-loglevel error` for quiet server logs. Panel centered with scrollable body |
|0.1.2 |2026-04-14 |Video pipeline: frame extraction (ffmpeg), interactive thumbnail selection panel, finalize route (resize + move to `_generated/`). New `select` step type in executor/client. Browser-side message handlers startup module. Configurable video settings (thumb toggle, frame interval, max dimension for downscale). `force_original_aspect_ratio` for downscale (no upscaling, aspect-safe). Executor timeout increased to 5min. `scanDirectory` supports configurable extensions |
|0.1.1 |2026-04-09 |Dropzone-level LLM config: 3-tier priority (step > dropzone > global) for provider, model, system-prompt |
|0.1.0 |2026-04-08 |Initial release: pipeline executor, route, client library. Command steps (thumbnails, text extraction, format conversion, image extraction). LLM steps (auto + interactive modes). Default pipelines for PDF, DOCX, XLSX, images. Prompt template system. Settings UI |"},"$:/config/rimir/file-pipeline/default-actions":{"title":"$:/config/rimir/file-pipeline/default-actions","type":"application/json","text":"{
    "thumb-image": {
        "command": "magick {{input}} -auto-orient -thumbnail \"{{resolution}}>\" {{output}}",
        "params": ["input", "output", "resolution"],
        "description": "Generate image thumbnail. -auto-orient applies the EXIF orientation tag so portrait-tagged images render upright"
    },
    "thumb-pdf": {
        "command": "bash -c 'out={{output}}; pdftoppm -png -f 1 -l 1 -singlefile -scale-to {{maxdim}} {{input}} \"${out%.png}\"'",
        "params": ["input", "output", "maxdim"],
        "description": "Generate PDF first-page thumbnail as PNG via pdftoppm (poppler-utils). Avoids the ImageMagick+Ghostscript png16malpha device compatibility issue"
    },
    "extract-pdf-text": {
        "command": "pdftotext -layout {{input}} -",
        "params": ["input"],
        "description": "Extract text from PDF via pdftotext"
    },
    "extract-pdf-images": {
        "command": "pdfimages -png {{input}} {{output}}",
        "params": ["input", "output"],
        "description": "Extract embedded images from PDF via pdfimages"
    },
    "convert-docx-to-pdf": {
        "command": "libreoffice --headless --convert-to pdf --outdir {{output}} {{input}}",
        "params": ["input", "output"],
        "description": "Convert DOCX to PDF via LibreOffice"
    },
    "extract-docx-text": {
        "command": "pandoc {{input}} -t markdown --wrap=none",
        "params": ["input"],
        "description": "Extract markdown from DOCX via pandoc"
    },
    "extract-xlsx-text": {
        "command": "python3 -c \"import openpyxl,sys;wb=openpyxl.load_workbook(sys.argv[1]);[print(f'## {ws.title}') or [print('|'.join(str(c.value or '') for c in r)) for r in ws.iter_rows()] for ws in wb]\" {{input}}",
        "params": ["input"],
        "description": "Extract text from XLSX via Python openpyxl"
    },
    "convert-doc-to-docx": {
        "command": "libreoffice --headless --convert-to docx --outdir {{output}} {{input}}",
        "params": ["input", "output"],
        "description": "Convert DOC to DOCX via LibreOffice"
    },
    "downscale-video": {
        "command": "bash -c 'for dim in {{dimensions}}; do ffmpeg -y -loglevel error -i {{input}} -vf \"scale=${dim}:${dim}:force_original_aspect_ratio=decrease:force_divisible_by=2\" -c:v libx264 -crf 23 -c:a aac {{output}}_${dim}.mp4; done'",
        "params": ["input", "output", "dimensions"],
        "description": "Downscale video to fit within max dimensions (no upscale)"
    },
    "extract-video-frames": {
        "command": "ffmpeg -y -loglevel error -i {{input}} -t 60 -vf \"fps=1/{{interval}}\" {{output}}_%03d.png",
        "params": ["input", "output", "interval"],
        "description": "Extract frames from first 60s of video"
    }
}
