File Pipeline provides configurable binary data processing pipelines for TiddlyWiki. It supports two types of processing steps:

* ''Command steps'' — run shell commands like ImageMagick, pdftotext, pandoc, or LibreOffice
* ''LLM steps'' — send extracted text to an LLM for analysis (auto-background or interactive with human-in-the-loop)

!! Architecture

The plugin has three layers:

* ''`pipeline-executor.js`'' (server) — loads pipeline definitions, runs command steps via `runner-actions.json`
* ''`pipeline-route.js`'' (server) — `POST /api/file-pipeline` endpoint, callable from any plugin
* ''`pipeline-client.js`'' (browser) — orchestrates the full flow: server call → artifact creation → LLM steps

!! Integration

When installed alongside ''file-upload'', all `<$file-dropzone>` widgets automatically trigger matching pipelines on upload. The file-upload thumbnail settings are replaced by file-pipeline's settings.

When installed alongside ''llm-connect'', document extraction uses pipelines instead of the legacy `/api/extract` route. Cached `.extracted` tiddlers are shared between both systems.

!! Pipeline Schema

Pipelines are defined as JSON tiddlers tagged `$:/tags/rimir/file-pipeline/pipeline`:

```json
{
  "name": "pipeline-name",
  "match": ["mime/type"],
  "steps": [
    {
      "id": "step-id",
      "action": "runner-action-name",
      "input": "source",
      "output": "_generated/{{name}}_thumb.png",
      "captureStdout": false,
      "scanDir": false,
      "condition": {"config": "$:/config/...", "equals": "yes"},
      "params": {"resolution": "{{config:$:/config/...}}"},
      "artifact": {"setField": "_thumbnail_uri"}
    }
  ]
}
```

!! Step Chaining

Steps reference each other via `"input": "step:<id>"`. The output of a command step (file path or captured stdout) becomes the input of the next step. This enables multi-stage workflows like DOC → DOCX → PDF → thumbnail.

!! LLM Steps

LLM steps send text from a previous step to an LLM API and store the response as an artifact. Two modes:

* ''Auto'' (`"mode": "auto"`) — runs in the background via `orchestrator.runAction()`, no user interaction
* ''Interactive'' (`"mode": "interactive"`) — opens a chat panel, user can change model, edit prompt, iterate, then save

LLM step fields: `promptTemplate` (tiddler title with `{{text}}`/`{{title}}`/`{{filename}}` substitution), `systemPrompt`, `provider`, `model`, `maxTokens`.

!! LLM Configuration Priority

LLM settings are resolved in this order (highest priority first):

# ''Step level'' — `systemPrompt`, `provider`, `model` fields in the pipeline step JSON (supports `{{config:...}}` indirection)
# ''Dropzone level'' — `prop-system-prompt`, `prop-provider`, `prop-model` attributes on `<$file-dropzone>`
# ''Global default'' — llm-connect's provider/model/system-prompt settings

This allows a single pipeline definition to be reused across different dropzones with different LLM configurations.

!! Artifact Lifecycle

All generated tiddlers carry `_artifact_source` (pointing to the original file) and `_artifact_type` fields. The file-upload plugin's cascade system automatically handles delete and rename propagation."},"$:/plugins/rimir/file-pipeline/documentation":{"title":"$:/plugins/rimir/file-pipeline/documentation","type":"text/vnd.tiddlywiki","text":"<$list filter="[[$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template]plugin-type[plugin]]" variable="ignore">
